---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout 
  title="About" 
  description="About Keishi's Blog: Why I write, what you'll find here, and how to connect."
>
  <div class="about-page">
    <section class="page-header">
      <div class="container">
        <h1 class="page-title">About This Blog</h1>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="about-content">
      <div class="container prose-container">
        <article class="prose">
          <h2>Why I Write</h2>
          <p>
            Writing is thinking made visible. It forces clarity—you can't hide behind vague ideas 
            when words demand precision. I write because it helps me understand the world better, 
            and because some ideas are worth sharing.
          </p>
          <p>
            This blog exists as a space for longer-form thinking that doesn't fit in tweets or 
            conversations. It's where I work through complex problems, document lessons learned, 
            and explore ideas that sit at the intersection of technology, systems, and human experience.
          </p>
          <p>
            I believe in clear, direct writing. No fluff, no unnecessary jargon. Technical depth 
            when the topic demands it, accessible language when it doesn't. I'd rather write one 
            useful piece than ten forgettable ones.
          </p>

          <h2>What You'll Find</h2>
          <p>
            Essays organized around five core themes:
          </p>
          <ul>
            <li><strong>Tech</strong> — Engineering, AI, tools, and the craft of building software</li>
            <li><strong>Systems</strong> — Mental models, processes, and frameworks for thinking</li>
            <li><strong>Society</strong> — Social issues, education, culture, and how we live together</li>
            <li><strong>Startups</strong> — The founder journey, lessons learned, building companies</li>
            <li><strong>Life</strong> — Personal essays, philosophy, and reflections on being human</li>
          </ul>
          <p>
            Most pieces are meant to be useful—either teaching something practical or providing 
            a new lens for seeing old problems. Some are more personal, documenting my own 
            journey and the mistakes I've made along the way.
          </p>

          <h2>About Me</h2>
          <p>
            I'm Keishi (Phạm Phan Anh)—a software engineer and founder based in Hanoi, Vietnam. 
            I'm currently in my final year studying Computer Science at HUST, working as a 
            Software Project Leader at Samsung, and co-founding two startups.
          </p>
          <p>
            I grew up with limited resources and taught myself to build things. That background 
            shaped how I think: pragmatic, resourceful, focused on what actually works. I believe 
            in using rationality to solve real problems and in building systems that make life 
            better for people.
          </p>
          <p>
            Learn more about my work at <a href="https://keishi.vercel.app/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">https://keishi.vercel.app/</a>.
          </p>

          <h2>Colophon</h2>
          <p>
            This blog is built with care using:
          </p>
          <ul>
            <li><strong>Framework:</strong> <a href="https://astro.build" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Astro</a> — static site generation for speed and simplicity</li>
            <li><strong>Styling:</strong> <a href="https://tailwindcss.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Tailwind CSS</a> — utility-first, customized for this design</li>
            <li><strong>CMS:</strong> <a href="https://decapcms.org" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Decap CMS</a> — git-backed content management</li>
            <li><strong>Fonts:</strong> Playfair Display, Source Serif 4, JetBrains Mono, Inter</li>
            <li><strong>Hosting:</strong> Vercel — fast global CDN</li>
          </ul>
          <p>
            The design aims for warmth and readability—like a quality notebook or Sunday paper. 
            Light mode uses warm paper tones; dark mode shifts to a sophisticated ink aesthetic.
          </p>

          <h2>Connect</h2>
          <div class="connect-links">
            <a href="https://keishi.vercel.app/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="connect-link">
              <span class="connect-arrow">→</span>
              <span class="connect-label">Portfolio</span>
              <span class="connect-value">https://keishi.vercel.app/</span>
            </a>
            <a href="https://github.com/VoidKeishi" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="connect-link">
              <span class="connect-arrow">→</span>
              <span class="connect-label">GitHub</span>
              <span class="connect-value">VoidKeishi</span>
            </a>
            <a href="mailto:phananha4@gmail.com" class="connect-link">
              <span class="connect-arrow">→</span>
              <span class="connect-label">Email</span>
              <span class="connect-value">phananha4@gmail.com</span>
            </a>
          </div>
        </article>
      </div>
    </section>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .about-page {
    padding-bottom: 4rem;
  }

  .page-header {
    padding: 4rem 0 3rem;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
  }

  .page-title {
    font-size: clamp(2rem, 4vw, 3rem);
    margin: 0;
  }

  .about-content {
    padding: 3rem 0;
  }

  .prose-container {
    max-width: 42rem;
  }

  .prose h2 {
    font-size: 1.5rem;
    margin-top: 3rem;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
    padding-bottom: 0.5rem;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
  }

  .prose h2:first-child {
    margin-top: 0;
  }

  .prose p {
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    line-height: 1.75;
  }

  .prose ul {
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    line-height: 1.75;
  }

  .prose li {
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }

  .prose strong {
    color: var(--text-primary);
    font-weight: 600;
  }

  .prose a {
    color: var(--accent);
    text-decoration: underline;
    text-decoration-color: var(--accent);
    text-underline-offset: 2px;
    transition: color var(--transition-fast);
  }

  .prose a:hover {
    color: var(--accent-hover);
  }

  /* Connect Links */
  .connect-links {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0.5rem;
    margin-top: 1.5rem;
  }

  .connect-link {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 0.75rem;
    padding: 0.875rem 1rem;
    background: var(--bg-secondary);
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    border-radius: var(--radius-md);
    text-decoration: none;
    transition: all var(--transition-base);
  }

  .connect-link:hover {
    background: var(--bg-elevated);
    border-color: var(--accent);
    transform: translateX(4px);
  }

  .connect-arrow {
    color: var(--accent);
    font-weight: 500;
  }

  .connect-label {
    font-family: var(--font-ui);
    font-size: 0.875rem;
    font-weight: 500;
    color: var(--text-primary);
    min-width: 5rem;
  }

  .connect-value {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.875rem;
    color: var(--text-muted);
  }
</style>

